10:
Men who came from the far away lands of Persia, Lud, and Put were soldiers in your army.\q1 They hung their shields and helmets on the walls of your city;
\q2 this caused many people to admire your city.
\q1

11:
Men from the cities of Arvad and Helek were watchmen on your city walls;\q2 men from the city of Gammad were in your towers.
\q1 They also hung their shields on your walls;
\q2 they also made your city very beautiful.

36:
The merchants of the other nations shake their heads\q2 because it is difficult for them to believe what has happened;
\q1 now your city has disappeared,
\q2 and it will not exist anymore."
